Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a medium #saucepan{} on medium-low heat. Add the onion to the pan and stir-fry until softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add the @couscous{120%g} to the pan and stir to coat.

Stir in the @boiled water{200%ml} and half the @chicken stock paste{20%g}. Pop a lid on the saucepan and remove from the heat.

Leave to the side for ~{8-10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Trim the @green beans{150%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @mustard seeds{1%sachet} and fry for ~{1%minute} more. Add a splash of water and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}.

Cook until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Transfer to a medium #bowl{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and cover to keep warm.

Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @North Indian style spice mix{1%sachet} and @tomato puree{30%g} to the pan. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @water{100%ml} and remaining chicken stock paste. Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir through the @mango chutney{40%g} and @butter{10%g} until melted, then remove from the heat. Add a splash of water to loosen if needed.

Fluff up the couscous with a #fork{}, stir through half the coriander and share between your bowls.

Top with the chicken and green beans.

Sprinkle over the remaining coriander to finish.

Enjoy!